files.name: spaceone/api/inventory/v1/collector.proto
files.description: A Collector is a plugin instance collecting cloud resources. A Collector can collect the resource data manually or by a pre-set schedule.

fields.name: project_id
fields.description:
if is_public is false, project_id is require
remained as is_public | True | False
+optional

methods.name: create
methods.description: Creates a new Collector with information of the plugin to use. Information of the plugin includes `version`, `provider`, and `upgrade_mode`.

methods.name: update
methods.description: Updates a specific Collector. You can make changes in Collector settings, including `name` and `tags`.

methods.name: update_plugin
methods.description: Updates the plugin of a specific Collector. This method resets the plugin data in the Collector to update the `metadata`.

methods.name: verify_plugin
methods.description: Verifies the plugin of a specific Collector. This method validates the plugin data, `version` and `endpoint`.

methods.name: delete
methods.description: Deletes a specific Collector. You must specify the `collector_id` of the Collector to delete.

methods.name: get
methods.description: Gets a specific Collector. Prints detailed information about the Collector, including its state, basic information, and the plugin information used for cloud resource collection.

methods.name: enable
methods.description: Enables a specific Collector. By enabling a Collector, you can communicate with a plugin used for collection.

methods.name: disable
methods.description: Disables a specific Collector. By disabling a Collector, you cannot communicate with a plugin used for collection.

methods.name: list
methods.description: Gets a list of all Collectors. You can use a query to get a filtered list of Collectors.

methods.name: add_schedule
methods.description: Adds a schedule to a specific Collector. When specifying the time to collect, the schedule is assigned in units of one hour.The specified schedule is applied every day.

methods.name: get_schedule
methods.description: Gets a specific schedule set in a specific Collector. You must specify the `collector_id` of the Collector and the `schedule_id` of the schedule.

methods.name: update_schedule
methods.description: Updates a specific schedule of the Collector. You can make changes in schedule settings, including `name` and collection time.

methods.name: delete_schedule
methods.description: Deletes a specific schedule of the Collector. You must specify the `schedule_id` of the schedule to delete.

methods.name: list_schedules
methods.description: Gets a list of all schedules set in a specific Collector. You must specify the `collector_id` of the Collector to get the schedule from.
